<article>
    <h1>Where to get Hong Kong snacks</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20200927/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-09-27"><time>2020-09-27</time></a>
        - <span>LIFE | FOOD &amp; DRINK</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>Hang He­ung Where:</p>
    <p>B4-33 Ion Or­chard, 2 Or­chard Turn</p>
    <p>Open: 11am to 9pm daily</p>
    <p>What to buy: Wife cake ($15 for a box of six) or a box of as­sorted freshly baked pas­tries that in­cludes mung bean paste cake, mini cen­tury egg cake and mini egg yolk cake at the same price.</p>
    <p>Joy Luck Tea­house Where:</p>
    <p>B4-61 Ion Or­chard, 2 Or­chard Turn</p>
    <p>Open: 9am to 10pm daily</p>
    <p>What to buy: Hoover egg tart ($2.30), Kam Kee Cafe pineapple bun ($2) and milk tea ($3.50 for hot and $3.80 for cold), Tak Hing’s curry fish ball ($4.80 a serv­ing).</p>
    <p>Tai Cheong Bak­ery Where:</p>
    <p>Four out­lets:</p>
    <p>31 Lorong Liput; B2 Takashimay­a Food Hall, 391 Or­chard Road;</p>
    <p>01-15 Square 2, 10 Si­naran Drive; B1-58 Raf­fles City Shop­ping Cen­tre, 252 North Bridge Road</p>
    <p>Open: Var­i­ous hours</p>
    <p>What to buy: Egg tart ($2)</p>
    <p>Honolulu Cafe Where:</p>
    <p>Two out­lets:</p>
    <p>01-33F The Cen­tre­point, 176 Or­chard Road; 02-06 West­gate, 3 Gate­way Drive</p>
    <p>Open: Var­i­ous hours</p>
    <p>What to buy: Egg tart ($1.70)</p>
    <p>Tsui Wah Where:</p>
    <p>Two out­lets:</p>
    <p>01-03 Clarke Quay, 3 River Val­ley Road; 02-02 The Heeren,</p>
    <p>260 Or­chard Road</p>
    <p>Open: Var­i­ous hours</p>
    <p>What to buy: Crispy bun with con­densed milk ($4.70 for take­away)</p>

